A joint operation of the Nigeria Police Force, Amotekun corps officials, hunters and vigilante men have rescued the second victim from Sunday’s kidnap incident in Osun State. DAILY POST had reported that gunmen on Sunday night abducted travellers along Omoh/Erin-Ijesha road, in Ori-Ade Local Government Area of Osun State. A police source told our correspondent that the gunmen kidnapped a man and a woman and took them to a nearby bush around Ori-Oke Omoh while others were left at the scene. The police on Monday rescued the man while the combined operations continued to comb the forest for the woman In a chat with DAILY POST, the spokesperson of the Osun State Command, Yemisi Opalola confirmed the rescue of the victim. She added that the Osun Joint Task Force, JTF was instrumental in the rescue operation. She maintained that “the Commissioner of Police vowed to ensure their release and make sure that the Osun Command is rid of every criminal activity. His word is his bond! Activities are ongoing to arrest the criminals.”